@DrJack: 

It's called a "hate card" for a reason. It gives players a huge bonus against certain cards to discourage players from them. If this makes you think twice about running lots of dual lands, then the card has done its job. No one says [autocard]Seedtime[/autocard] is broken because it costs the same as [autocard]Time Walk[/autocard]. No one says [autocard]Relic of Progenitus[/autocard] is broken because it kills dredge for 2 mana. No one says [autocard]Stony Silence[/autocard] is broken because it messes with artifacts at a cheap cost. Cards like these are all necessary for a balanced metagame because every deck has to think about what hate they'll run into, and if a single deck becomes too good, everyone can sideboard in hate to stop it.

Besides, it's not like this has done anything to stop Legacy's abundance of dual, fetch, utility, and man lands. Personally, I think that basic lands deserve more relevance in the metagame, especially since lands are quickly becoming the most expensive part of any competitive deck. Yes, this card is good enough to see some tournament action, (particularly in Delver deck) but it's nothing to get up in arms about.

